def decade(row):

    if row['day'] <= 10:
        return 1
    elif row['day'] > 10 and row['day'] <= 20:
        return 2
    else:
        return 3

def descriptive_statistics(values, label):
    '''
      ,    .

         .
     DataFrame   .

    '''

    df = pd.DataFrame([
        values.count(),
        len(values.unique()),
        values.min(),
        values.median() - 1.5 * (values.quantile(q=.75) -
                                 values.quantile(q=.25)),
        values.quantile(q=.25).round(2),
        (values.mode()).to_list(),
        values.median().round(2),
        values.mean().round(2),
        values.quantile(q=.75).round(2),
        values.median() + 1.5 * (values.quantile(q=.75) -
                                 values.quantile(q=.25)),
        values.max(),
        values.max() - values.min(),
        values.quantile(q=.75) - values.quantile(q=.25)
    ],
        index=['- ', '- ', '.',
               '-1.5IQR', '25 %', '', '',
               ' .', '75 %', '+1.5IQR', '.',
               '', ' '],
        columns=[label])

    return df

def cv_score(model, X=features_train, y=target_train):
    '''
        (RMSE) ,
       -.

        
    ( -  ).
         (RMSE).
    '''

    return abs(cross_val_score(model, X=X, y=y,
                               cv=tscv, n_jobs=-1, error_score='raise',
                               scoring='neg_root_mean_squared_error').mean())

In [65]:
class DummyRegressor(BaseEstimator, RegressorMixin):
    '''
      ,  
      ,   .

    strategy:  integer,   1.
     ,   .
    '''

    def __init__(self, strategy=1):

        self.strategy = strategy

    def fit(self, X, y=None):

        return self

    def predict(self, X):

        return X[f'lag_{self.strategy}']

Стохастический градиентный спуск¶

In [69]:
%%time

model_sgdr = SGDRegressor(random_state=RANDOM_STATE)
pipeliner = make_pipeline(transformer, model_sgdr)

parameters = {'sgdregressor__alpha': [10**n for n in range(1, -7, -1)],
              'sgdregressor__tol': [10**n for n in range(1, -6, -1)],
              'sgdregressor__eta0': [10**n for n in range(1, -4, -1)]}

sgdr = RandomizedSearchCV(pipeliner, param_distributions=parameters, cv=tscv,
